### Abstract (250 words)

**Template:**

```
[Background - 2 sentences]
The proliferation of cyber fraud in India has created a regulatory dilemma: 
banks must prevent financial crimes while respecting account holders' 
property rights. [Context: Kerala HC judgment, regulatory gap]

[Research Question - 1 sentence]
This study examines: [Your specific RQ]

[Methodology - 2 sentences]
Using gap analysis methodology, this research analyzed [X] High Court 
judgments spanning 2020-2025 and compared India's framework with 
international best practices. [Data collection method]

[Key Findings - 3 sentences]
Analysis reveals five critical regulatory gaps: [List briefly]. 
[Statistical finding: e.g., X% cases without LE involvement].
Courts have responded by creating ad-hoc rules, with Kerala HC's 
2024 judgment establishing interim guidelines.

[Contribution - 2 sentences]
This study proposes a comprehensive RBI Master Direction providing 
clear authority, procedural safeguards, time limits (90 days), 
accountability mechanisms, and coordination protocols. 
[Implementation significance]

Keywords: Account freezing, cyber crime, regulatory gap, banking 
law, RBI guidelines, money mules, gap analysis
```

**Your Draft:**
[Write here once you have all findings]

