#### **Chapter 3: Methodology (3-4 pages)**

**Source:** Primarily NEW writing, but describing what you did in Weeks 1-4

**3.1 Research Design: Gap Analysis (1 page)**
- Explain gap analysis as a framework
- Why appropriate for this research
- Five-dimensional structure introduced
- Visual: Include your gap map diagram

**3.2 Data Collection (1 page)**
- India Kanoon search strategy
- 14 search queries (list them)
- Time period: 2020-2025 (rationale)
- Courts covered
- Initial results: X citations ‚Üí Y relevant cases

**3.3 Case Selection Criteria (0.5 page)**
- Inclusion criteria (specific)
- Exclusion criteria
- Rapid screening protocol
- Final sample: Z cases for deep analysis

**3.4 Analysis Methods (1 page)**
- **Qualitative:** Deep reading, thematic coding, gap identification
- **Quantitative:** Descriptive statistics, frequency analysis
- **Comparative:** India vs. international standards
- **Normative:** Policy design based on evidence

**3.5 Limitations (0.5 page)**
- No empirical data from banks (future research)
- No stakeholder interviews (future research)
- Limited to doctrinal and judicial analysis
- Time period (may have missed recent cases)
- Geographic scope (Indian courts only)

**THIS IS YOUR SHOWCASE SECTION**
**Polish Checklist:**
- [ ] Shows systematic approach
- [ ] Replicable by others
- [ ] Acknowledges limitations honestly
- [ ] Demonstrates rigor
- [ ] Explains database structure briefly

