#### **Chapter 6: Proposed Framework (10-12 pages)**

**Source:** From `week4_proposed_framework.md`

**6.1 Design Principles (1 page)**
- Balance (crime prevention ‚Üî rights)
- Clarity (specific vs. vague)
- Enforceability (accountability)
- Coordination (bank-police cooperation)
- Flexibility (urgent action + safeguards)

**6.2 Draft RBI Master Direction (4-5 pages)**

**Don't** include full text here (that's Appendix C)

**Do** present highlights of each section:

```
**Section 1: Definitions**
Key: "Suspicious Account Operations" defined as [specific criteria]
vs. current vague "appropriate action"

**Section 2: Authority to Freeze**
Key: Banks may freeze when [conditions], by [authorized officials]
Rationale: [Why this solves authority gap]

**Section 3: Procedural Requirements**
Key: Notice within 24 hours, right to explain (7 days), 
bank decision (7 days)
Rationale: [Why this solves procedural gap]

**Section 4: Time Limits**
Key: Maximum 90 days, automatic de-freeze if no LE action
Rationale: [Why this solves temporal gap]

[Continue for Sections 5-9]
```

**6.3 Provision-by-Provision Rationale (3-4 pages)**

Pick 5-7 key provisions and explain deeply:

**Example:**
```
**Provision: 90-Day Maximum Duration**

**Gap Addressed:** Currently no time limit; cases show freezes 
of 1+ years

**Evidence Base:** 
- Average freeze in our data: [X] days
- [Y%] of cases exceeded one year
- Kerala HC adopted 3-month rule
- UK FCA has similar limit

**How It Works:**
[Explain the provision]

**Expected Impact:**
- Prevents indefinite deprivation
- Forces timely action by banks and police
- Protects [Article 300A] rights
- Still allows genuine investigations (extension with LE involvement)

**Implementation Challenge:** [If any]
**Solution:** [How provision addresses it]
```

**6.4 Comparison with Current Situation (2 pages)**

**Big comparison table:**

| Issue | Current RBI | Kerala HC | Proposed | Advantage |
|-------|------------|-----------|----------|-----------|
| Authority | Vague | Implicit | Explicit with criteria | [Explain] |
| Notice | Only KYC | Same day | Same day + detailed | [Explain] |
| Time limit | None | 3 months | 90 days + extensions | [Explain] |
| Accountability | None | None | Compensation + penalties | [Explain] |
| Coordination | Vague | Report to cyber police | Structured protocol | [Explain] |

**6.5 Implementation Considerations (1-2 pages)**

**Challenges and Solutions:**
- Banks may resist: [Solution]
- Police capacity: [Solution]
- Technology needs: [Solution]
- Training required: [Solution]
- Transition period: [Solution]

**Monitoring and Review:**
- RBI oversight mechanism
- Annual reporting
- Framework evolution

**Polish Checklist:**
- [ ] Proposed framework clear
- [ ] Each provision justified by evidence
- [ ] Not just describing, but arguing for adoption
- [ ] Practical implementation considered
- [ ] Connects back to gaps identified

